    • Constructor Detail

      • IOFileIterator

        public IOFileIterator(File directory,
              String... extensions)
        Allows iteration over the files in a given directory (no recursive) which match an array of extensions.
        Parameters:
        directory - the directory to search in
        extensions - an array of extensions, ex. {"java","xml"}. If this parameter is null, all files are returned.

      • IOFileIterator

        public IOFileIterator(File directory,
              boolean recursive,
              String... extensions)
        Allows iteration over the files in a given directory (and optionally its sub directories) which match an array of extensions.
        Parameters:
        directory - the directory to search in
        extensions - an array of extensions, ex. {"java","xml"}. If this parameter is null, all files are returned.
        recursive - if true all sub directories are searched as well

      • IOFileIterator

        public IOFileIterator(File directory,
              boolean recursive,
              IOFileFilter fileFilter)
        Allows iteration over the files in given directory (and optionally its sub directories).

        All files found are filtered by an IOFileFilter.

        Parameters:
        directory - the directory to search in
        fileFilter - filter to apply when finding files.
        recursive - if true all sub directories are searched as well
        See Also:
        FileFilters, NameFileFilter

      • IOFileIterator

        public IOFileIterator(File directory,
              IOFileFilter fileFilter,
              IOFileFilter dirFilter)
        Allows iteration over the files in given directory (and optionally its sub directories).

        All files found are filtered by an IOFileFilter.

        Parameters:
        directory - the directory to search in
        fileFilter - filter to apply when finding files.
        dirFilter - optional filter to apply when finding sub directories. If this parameter is null, sub directories will not be included in the search. Use TrueFileFilter.INSTANCE to match all directories.
        See Also:
        FileFilters, NameFileFilter

      • IOFileIterator

        public IOFileIterator(File directory,
              IOFileFilter fileFilter,
              IOFileFilter dirFilter,
              boolean incdir)
        Allows iteration over the files in given directory (and optionally its sub directories).

        All files found are filtered by an IOFileFilter.

        Parameters:
        directory - the directory to search in
        fileFilter - filter to apply when finding files.
        dirFilter - optional filter to apply when finding sub directories. If this parameter is null, sub directories will not be included in the search. Use TrueFileFilter.INSTANCE to match all directories.
        incdir - if true all sub directories are included as well
        See Also:
        FileFilters, NameFileFilter
